theorem Topology.dense_union {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    Dense A → Dense B → Dense (A ∪ B) := by
  intro hA hB
  have hclosure : closure (A ∪ B) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    calc
      closure (A ∪ B) = closure A ∪ closure B := by
        simpa using closure_union (s := A) (t := B)
      _ = (Set.univ : Set X) ∪ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
        simpa [hA.closure_eq, hB.closure_eq]
      _ = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
        simp
  simpa [Dense] using hclosure

theorem Topology.dense_interior_of_P1_and_dense {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) (hDense : Dense A) : Dense (interior A) := by
  -- From `P1` we have `A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have h_subset : A ⊆ closure (interior A) := hP1
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
  have h_closure_subset : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
    closure_mono h_subset
  -- Since `A` is dense, `closure A = Set.univ`.
  have h_univ_subset : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
    simpa [hDense.closure_eq] using h_closure_subset
  -- Establish the desired equality of sets.
  have h_eq : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · intro _ _; simp
    · exact h_univ_subset
  -- Reformulate the equality as the `Dense` property.
  simpa [Dense] using h_eq

theorem Topology.closure_diff_subset_closure_diff {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A \ B) ⊆ closure A \ interior B := by
  intro x hx
  -- First, `x` belongs to `closure A`.
  have h₁ : x ∈ closure A := by
    have h_subset : (A \ B) ⊆ A := by
      intro y hy
      exact hy.1
    exact (closure_mono h_subset) hx
  -- Next, prove `x ∉ interior B`.
  have h₂ : x ∉ interior B := by
    intro hxInt
    -- Consider the open set `interior B` that contains `x`.
    have h_nonempty : ((interior B) ∩ (A \ B)).Nonempty := by
      have h_open : IsOpen (interior B) := isOpen_interior
      exact (mem_closure_iff).1 hx (interior B) h_open hxInt
    -- Extract a witness from the non-empty intersection.
    rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, ⟨hyIntB, hyDiff⟩⟩
    -- From `y ∈ interior B`, we get `y ∈ B`.
    have hy_in_B : y ∈ B := interior_subset hyIntB
    -- From `y ∈ A \\ B`, we know `y ∉ B`.
    have hy_not_B : y ∉ B := hyDiff.2
    exact hy_not_B hy_in_B
  exact And.intro h₁ h₂
